\title{Second Opinion}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Runs external LLM code reviews (OpenAI Codex or Google Gemini CLI) on uncommitted changes, branch diffs, or specific commits. Use when the user asks for a second opinion, external review, codex review, gemini review, or mentions /second-opinion."}

\subtree{
\title{Second Opinion}
\p{Shell out to external LLM CLIs for an independent code review powered by a separate model. Supports OpenAI Codex CLI and Google Gemini CLI.}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use}
\ul{
\li{Getting a second opinion on code changes from a different model}
\li{Reviewing branch diffs before opening a PR}
\li{Checking uncommitted work for issues before committing}
\li{Running a focused review (security, performance, error handling)}
\li{Comparing review output from multiple models}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{When NOT to Use}
\ul{
\li{Neither Codex CLI nor Gemini CLI is installed}
\li{No API key or subscription configured for either tool}
\li{Reviewing non-code files (documentation, config)}
\li{You want Claude's own review (just ask Claude directly)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Safety Note}
\p{Gemini CLI is invoked with \code{\startverb --yolo\stopverb}, which auto-approves all tool calls without confirmation. This is required for headless (non-interactive) operation but means Gemini will execute any tool actions its extensions request without prompting.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Reference}
\pre{\startverb
# Codex (headless exec with structured JSON output)
codex exec --sandbox read-only --ephemeral \
  --output-schema codex-review-schema.json \
  -o "$output_file" - < "$prompt_file"

# Gemini (code review extension)
gemini -p "/code-review" --yolo -e code-review
# Gemini (headless with diff — see references/ for full pattern)
git diff HEAD > /tmp/review-diff.txt
{ printf '%s\n\n' 'Review this diff for issues.'; cat /tmp/review-diff.txt; } \
  | gemini -p - --yolo -m gemini-3.1-pro-preview
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Invocation}
\subtree{
\title{1. Gather context interactively}
\p{Use \code{\startverb AskUserQuestion\stopverb} to collect review parameters in one shot. Adapt the questions based on what the user already provided in their invocation (skip questions they already answered).}

\p{Combine all applicable questions into a single \code{\startverb AskUserQuestion\stopverb} call (max 4 questions).}

\p{\strong{Question 1 — Tool} (skip if user already specified):}

\pre{\startverb
header: "Review tool"
question: "Which tool should run the review?"
options:
  - "Both Codex and Gemini (Recommended)" → run both in parallel
  - "Codex only"                          → codex exec
  - "Gemini only"                         → gemini CLI
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Question 2 — Scope} (skip if user already specified):}

\pre{\startverb
header: "Review scope"
question: "What should be reviewed?"
options:
  - "Uncommitted changes" → git diff HEAD + untracked files
  - "Branch diff vs main" → git diff <branch>...HEAD (auto-detect default branch)
  - "Specific commit"     → git diff <sha>~1..<sha> (follow up for SHA)
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Question 3 — Project context} (skip if neither CLAUDE.md nor AGENTS.md exists):}

\p{Check for CLAUDE.md first, then AGENTS.md in the repo root. Only show this question if at least one exists.}

\pre{\startverb
header: "Project context"
question: "Include project conventions file so the review
  checks against your standards?"
options:
  - "Yes, include it"
  - "No, standard review"
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Question 4 — Review focus} (always ask):}

\pre{\startverb
header: "Review focus"
question: "Any specific focus areas for the review?"
options:
  - "General review"    → no custom prompt
  - "Security & auth"   → security-focused prompt
  - "Performance"       → performance-focused prompt
  - "Error handling"    → error handling-focused prompt
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Run the tool directly}
\p{Do not pre-check tool availability. Run the selected tool immediately. If the command fails with "command not found" or an extension is missing, report the install command from the Error Handling table below and skip that tool (if "Both" was selected, run only the available one).}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Diff Preview}
\p{After collecting answers, show the diff stats:}

\pre{\startverb
# For uncommitted (tracked + untracked):
git diff --stat HEAD
git ls-files --others --exclude-standard

# For branch diff:
git diff --stat <branch>...HEAD

# For specific commit:
git diff --stat <sha>~1..<sha>
\stopverb}

\p{If the diff is empty, stop and tell the user.}

\p{If the diff is very large (>2000 lines changed), warn the user and ask whether to proceed or narrow the scope.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Skipping Inapplicable Checks}
\p{After determining the diff scope, skip checks that don't apply to the files actually changed.}

\subtree{
\title{Dependency Scanning}
\p{Only run \code{\startverb /security:scan-deps\stopverb} when the diff touches dependency manifest files. Check with:}

\pre{\startverb
git diff --name-only <scope> \
  | grep -qiE '(package\.json|package-lock|yarn\.lock|pnpm-lock|Gemfile|\.gemspec|requirements\.txt|setup\.py|setup\.cfg|pyproject\.toml|poetry\.lock|uv\.lock|Cargo\.toml|Cargo\.lock|go\.mod|go\.sum|composer\.json|composer\.lock|Pipfile)'
\stopverb}

\p{If no dependency files are in the diff, skip the scan even when security focus is selected. The scan analyzes the entire project's dependency tree regardless of diff scope, so it adds significant time for zero value when dependencies weren't touched.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Auto-detect Default Branch}
\p{For branch diff scope, detect the default branch name:}

\pre{\startverb
git symbolic-ref refs/remotes/origin/HEAD 2>/dev/null \
  | sed 's@^refs/remotes/origin/@@' || echo main
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Codex Invocation}
\p{See [references/codex-invocation.md](references/codex-invocation.md) for full details on command syntax, prompt assembly, and the structured output schema.}

\p{Summary:}

\ul{
\li{Uses \code{\startverb codex exec\stopverb} (not \code{\startverb codex review\stopverb}) for headless operation}
\li{Model: \code{\startverb gpt-5.3-codex\stopverb}, reasoning: \code{\startverb xhigh\stopverb}}
\li{Uses OpenAI's published code review prompt (fine-tuned into the model)}
\li{Diff is generated manually and piped via stdin with the prompt}
\li{\code{\startverb --output-schema\stopverb} produces structured JSON findings}
\li{\code{\startverb -o\stopverb} captures only the final message (no thinking/exec noise)}
\li{All three scopes (uncommitted, branch, commit) support project}
\li{Falls back to \code{\startverb gpt-5.2-codex\stopverb} on auth errors}
\li{Output is clean JSON — parse and present findings by priority}
\li{Set \code{\startverb timeout: 600000\stopverb} on the Bash call}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Gemini Invocation}
\p{See [references/gemini-invocation.md](references/gemini-invocation.md) for full details on flags, scope mapping, and extension usage.}

\p{Summary:}

\ul{
\li{Model: \code{\startverb gemini-3.1-pro-preview\stopverb}, flags: \code{\startverb --yolo\stopverb}, \code{\startverb -e\stopverb}, \code{\startverb -m\stopverb}}
\li{For uncommitted general review: \code{\startverb gemini -p "/code-review" --yolo -e code-review\stopverb}}
\li{For branch/commit diffs: pipe \code{\startverb git diff\stopverb} into \code{\startverb gemini -p\stopverb}}
\li{Security extension name is \code{\startverb gemini-cli-security\stopverb} (not \code{\startverb security\stopverb})}
\li{\code{\startverb /security:analyze\stopverb} is interactive-only — use \code{\startverb -p\stopverb} with a}
\li{Run \code{\startverb /security:scan-deps\stopverb} only when security focus is selected}
\li{Set \code{\startverb timeout: 600000\stopverb} on the Bash call}
}

\p{\strong{Scope mapping for \code{\startverb git diff\stopverb}} (Gemini has no built-in scope flags):}

\pre{\startverb
| Scope | Diff command |
|-------|-------------|
| Uncommitted | `git diff HEAD` + untracked (see codex-invocation.md) |
| Branch diff | `git diff <branch>...HEAD` |
| Specific commit | `git diff <sha>~1..<sha>` |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Running Both}
\p{When the user picks "Both" (the default):}

\ol{
\li{Run Codex and Gemini in parallel — issue both Bash tool}
\li{Collect both results, then present with clear headers:}
}

\pre{\startverb
## Codex Review (gpt-5.3-codex)
<codex output>

## Gemini Review (gemini-3.1-pro-preview)
<gemini output>
\stopverb}

\p{Summarize where the two reviews agree and differ.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Error Handling}
\pre{\startverb
| Error | Action |
|-------|--------|
| `codex: command not found` | Tell user: `npm i -g @openai/codex` |
| `gemini: command not found` | Tell user: `npm i -g @google/gemini-cli` |
| Gemini `code-review` extension missing | Tell user: `gemini extensions install https://github.com/gemini-cli-extensions/code-review` |
| Gemini `gemini-cli-security` extension missing | Tell user: `gemini extensions install https://github.com/gemini-cli-extensions/security` |
| Model auth error (Codex) | Retry with `gpt-5.2-codex` |
| Empty diff | Tell user there are no changes to review |
| Timeout | Inform user and suggest narrowing the diff scope |
| Tool partially unavailable | Run only the available tool, note the skip |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Examples}
\p{\strong{Both tools (default):}}

\pre{\startverb
User: /second-opinion
Claude: [asks 4 questions: tool, scope, context, focus]
User: picks "Both", "Branch diff", "Yes include CLAUDE.md", "Security"
Claude: [detects default branch = main]
Claude: [shows diff --stat: 6 files, +103 -15]
Claude: [assembles prompt with review instructions + CLAUDE.md + security focus + diff]
Claude: [runs codex exec and gemini in parallel]
Claude: [reads codex output file, parses structured findings]
Claude: [presents both reviews, highlights agreements/differences]
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Codex only with inline args:}}

\pre{\startverb
User: /second-opinion check uncommitted changes for bugs
Claude: [scope known: uncommitted, focus known: custom]
Claude: [asks 2 questions: tool, project context]
User: picks "Codex only", "No context"
Claude: [shows diff --stat: 3 files, +45 -10]
Claude: [writes prompt file with review instructions + diff]
Claude: [runs codex exec, reads structured JSON output]
Claude: [presents findings by priority with file:line refs]
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Gemini only:}}

\pre{\startverb
User: /second-opinion
Claude: [asks 4 questions]
User: picks "Gemini only", "Uncommitted", "No", "General"
Claude: [shows diff --stat: 2 files, +20 -5]
Claude: [runs gemini -p "/code-review" --yolo -e code-review]
Claude: [presents review]
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Large diff warning:}}

\pre{\startverb
User: /second-opinion
Claude: [asks questions] → user picks "Both", "Uncommitted", "General"
Claude: [shows diff --stat: 45 files, +3200 -890]
Claude: "Large diff (3200+ lines). Proceed, or narrow the scope?"
User: "proceed"
Claude: [runs both reviews]
\stopverb}
}
}